{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I am the man who has seen afflictionby the rod of his wrath."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has led me and caused me to walk in darkness, and not in light."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Surely he turns his hand against meagain and again all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has made my flesh and my skin old. He has broken my bones."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has built against me, and surrounded me with bitterness and hardship."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has made me dwell in dark places, as those who have been long dead."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has walled me about, so that I can’t go out. He has made my chain heavy."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yes, when I cry, and call for help, he shuts out my prayer."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has walled up my ways with cut stone. He has made my paths crooked."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He is to me as a bear lying in wait, as a lion in hiding."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has turned away my path, and pulled me in pieces."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has made me desolate."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has bent his bow, and set me as a mark for the arrow."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has caused the shafts of his quiver to enter into my kidneys."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I have become a derision to all my people,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "and their song all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has filled me with bitterness. He has stuffed me with wormwood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He has also broken my teeth with gravel. He has covered me with ashes."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have removed my soul far away from peace. I forgot prosperity."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I said, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "My strength has perished, along with my expectation from Yahweh.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Remember my affliction and my misery, the wormwood and the bitterness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul still remembers them, and is bowed down within me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "This I recall to my mind; therefore I have hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is because of Yahweh’s loving kindnesses that we are not consumed, because his mercies don’t fail."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They are new every morning. Great is your faithfulness."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Yahweh is my portion,",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "says my soul."
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Therefore I will hope in him.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh is good to those who wait for him, to the soul who seeks him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is good that a man should hope and quietly wait for the salvation of Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "It is good for a man that he bear the yoke in his youth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him sit alone and keep silence, because he has laid it on him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "29",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him put his mouth in the dust, if it is so that there may be hope."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "30",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let him give his cheek to him who strikes him. Let him be filled full of reproach."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "31",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For the Lord will not cast off forever."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "32",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For though he causes grief,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "yet he will have compassion according to the multitude of his loving kindnesses."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "33",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "For he does not afflict willingly, nor grieve the children of men."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "34",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "To crush under foot all the prisoners of the earth,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "35",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to turn away the right of a man before the face of the Most High,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "36",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "to subvert a man in his cause, the Lord doesn’t approve."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "37",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Who is he who says, and it comes to pass, when the Lord doesn’t command it?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "38",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Doesn’t evil and good come out of the mouth of the Most High?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "39",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Why should a living man complain,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "a man for the punishment of his sins?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "40",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let us search and try our ways, and turn again to Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "41",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Let’s lift up our heart with our hands to God[^3] in the heavens."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "42",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "We have transgressed and have rebelled. \nYou have not pardoned.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "43",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "“You have covered us with anger and pursued us. You have killed. \nYou have not pitied.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "44",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have covered yourself with a cloud, so that no prayer can pass through.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "45",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "You have made us an off-scouring and refusein the middle of the peoples.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "46",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "“All our enemies have opened their mouth wide against us.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "47",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Terror and the pit have come on us, \ndevastation and destruction.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "48",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eye runs down with streams of water, for the destruction of the daughter of my people."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "49",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eye pours down and doesn’t cease,"
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "without any intermission,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "50",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "until Yahweh looks down, and sees from heaven."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "51",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My eye affects my soul, because of all the daughters of my city."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "52",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have chased me relentlessly like a bird, those who are my enemies without cause."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "53",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "They have cut off my life in the dungeon, and have cast a stone on me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "54",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Waters flowed over my head. I said, "
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "I am cut off.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "55",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I called on your name, Yahweh, out of the lowest dungeon."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "56",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You heard my voice:\n"
        },
        {
          "type": "prayer",
          "text": "Don’t hide your ear from my sighing, \nand my cry.",
          "speaker": "Unknown"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "57",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You came near in the day that I called on you. You said, "
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "Don’t be afraid.",
          "speaker": "The LORD"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "58",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Lord, you have pleaded the causes of my soul. You have redeemed my life."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "59",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Yahweh, you have seen my wrong. Judge my cause."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "60",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have seen all their vengeance and all their plans against me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "61",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You have heard their reproach, Yahweh, and all their plans against me,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "62",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "the lips of those that rose up against me, and their plots against me all day long."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "63",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You see their sitting down and their rising up. I am their song."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "64",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You will pay them back, Yahweh, according to the work of their hands."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "65",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You will give them hardness of heart, your curse to them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "66",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "You will pursue them in anger, and destroy them from under the heavens of Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}